The paper discusses constructing and maintaining knowledge of the world using predictions, which is a central problem in artificial intelligence research. The approach discussed in the paper, General Value Functions (GVFs), is commonly used in reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.RO. The paper also discusses evaluating predictions in terms of how they are used, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SY and cs.NE, as these fields deal with systems and networks that use predictions.
